'''Ermedin Demirović''' ({{IPA|bs|ermědin děmiroʋitɕ|pron}}; born 25 March 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfB Stuttgart]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Demirović started his professional career at [[RB Leipzig]], playing mainly in its [[RB Leipzig affiliated teams#Reserve team|reserve team]], before joining [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]] in 2017. He was loaned to [[FC Sochaux-Montbéliard|Sochaux]] in 2018, to [[UD Almería|Almería]] in 2019 and to [[FC St. Gallen|St. Gallen]] later that year. In 2020, he moved to [[SC Freiburg]]. Two years later, Demirović signed with [[FC Augsburg]]. In 2024, he was transferred to VfB Stuttgart.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Demirović made his senior international debut in 2021, earning over 30 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Demirović started playing football at his hometown club [[Hamburger SV]], before joining [[RB Leipzig affiliated teams#Youth academy|RB Leipzig's youth academy]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/421996/demirovic-otkriva-kako-je-odbio-poziv-velesile-ja-sam-bosanac-ne-mogu-igrati-za-njemacku|title=Demirović otkriva kako je odbio poziv velesile: Ja sam Bosanac, ne mogu igrati za Njemačku|website=avaz.ba|date=12 October 2018|access-date=12 October 2018|language=bs}}</ref>

===Alavés===
In May, Demirović signed a four-year deal with Spanish team [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/mladi-bh-reprezentativac-ermedin-demirovic-potpisao-za-alaves/170530073|title=Mladi bh. reprezentativac Ermedin Demirović potpisao za Alavés|website=klix.ba|date=30 May 2017|access-date=1 June 2017|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut in a [[2017–18 Copa del Rey#Round of 16|Copa del Rey]] game against [[SD Formentera|Formentera]] on 3 January 2018 and scored a brace.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/demirovic-s-dva-gola-zablistao-u-debiju-za-deportivo-alaves/263739|title=Demirović s dva gola zablistao u debiju za Deportivo Alavés|website=sportsport.ba|date=3 January 2018|access-date=3 January 2018|language=bs}}</ref> Three weeks later, he made his league debut against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/242643-demirovic-zaigrao-protiv-barcelone-na-kraju-razmijenio-dres-s-rakiticem|title=Demirović zaigrao protiv Barcelone, na kraju razmijenio dres s Rakitićem|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=29 January 2018|access-date=1 February 2018|language=bs}}</ref> On 6 May, he scored his first league goal in a triumph over [[Málaga CF|Málaga]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/demirovic-zabio-prvijenac-u-la-ligi-i-to-kakav|title=Demirović zabio prvijenac u La Ligi i to kakav|website=sportske.ba|date=6 May 2018|access-date=9 May 2018|language=bs}}</ref>

In July, Demirović was loaned to French side [[FC Sochaux-Montbéliard|Sochaux]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/alaves-demirovica-posudio-u-francusku/1176018|title=Alavés Demirovića posudio u Francusku|website=fokus.ba|date=24 July 2018|access-date=27 July 2018|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2019, he was sent on a six-month loan to [[UD Almería|Almería]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/450228/nova-posudba-ermedin-demirovic-do-kraja-sezone-u-almeriji|title=Nova posudba: Ermedin Demirović do kraja sezone u Almeríji|website=avaz.ba|date=17 January 2019|access-date=18 January 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

In September, he was loaned to Swiss outfit [[FC St. Gallen|St. Gallen]] for the remainder of the campaign.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/ermedin-demirovic-presao-iz-spanije-u-svicarsku/23683|title=Ermedin Demirović prešao iz Španije u Švicarsku|website=faktor.ba|date=3 September 2019|access-date=3 September 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

===SC Freiburg===
In July 2020, Demirović was transferred to [[SC Freiburg]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/ermedin-demirovic-potpisao-za-freiburg/369948|title=Ermedin Demirović potpisao za Freiburg|website=sportsport.ba|date=28 July 2020|access-date=30 July 2020|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the club in a [[2020–21 DFB-Pokal#First round|DFB-Pokal]] match against [[SV Waldhof Mannheim|Waldhof Mannheim]] on 13 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/308743-ermedin-demirovic-odigrao-prvu-zvanicnu-utakmicu-za-freiburg|title=Ermedin Demirović odigrao prvu zvaničnu utakmicu za Freiburg|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=13 September 2020|access-date=15 September 2020|language=bs}}</ref> Two weeks later, he made his league debut against [[VfL Wolfsburg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/ermedin-demirovic-upisao-bundesligaski-debi-freiburg-remizirao-s-wolfsburgom|title=Ermedin Demirović upisao bundesligaški debi, Freiburg remizirao s Wolfsburgom|website=scsport.ba|date=27 September 2020|access-date=27 September 2020|language=bs}}</ref> On 20 December, he scored his first goal for SC Freiburg in a defeat of [[Hertha BSC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/demirovic-postigao-prvijenac-za-freiburg/1951493|title=Demirović postigao prvijenac za Freiburg|website=fokus.ba|date=20 December 2020|access-date=21 December 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

===FC Augsburg===
In July 2022, Demirović switched to [[FC Augsburg]] on a contract until June 2026.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/saga-je-gotova-ermedin-demirovic-ima-novi-klub/462586|title=Saga je gotova: Ermedin Demirović ima novi klub|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=8 July 2022|access-date=9 July 2022|language=bs}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the squad in a [[2022–23 DFB-Pokal#First round|DFB-Pokal]] tie on 31 July against [[Blau-Weiß Lohne]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/366381-kup-njemacke-demirovic-starter-augsburg-rutinski-prosao-u-1-16-finala|title=Kup Njemačke: Demirović starter, Augsburg rutinski prošao u 1/16 finala|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=31 July 2022|access-date=1 August 2022|language=bs}}</ref> A week later, he made his league debut against SC Freiburg.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/763492/demirovicev-debi-za-augsburg-u-sjeni-teskog-poraza-od-njegovog-bivseg-kluba-freiburga|title=Demirovićev debi za Augsburg u sjeni teškog poraza od njegovog bivšeg kluba Freiburga|website=avaz.ba|date=6 August 2022|access-date=9 August 2022|language=bs}}</ref> On 20 August, he scored his first goal for FC Augsburg against [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/ermedin-demirovic-postigao-spektakularan-gol-petom-u-bundesligi-prvijenac-za-novi-klub/220820057|title=Ermedin Demirović postigao spektakularan gol petom u Bundesligi, prvijenac za novi klub|website=klix.ba|date=20 August 2022|access-date=21 August 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

In August 2023, he was named team [[Captain (association football)|captain]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/demirovic-imenovan-za-kapitena-augsburga-ponosan-sam-sto-cu-predvoditi-tim|title=Demirović imenovan za kapitena Augsburga: Ponosan sam što ću predvoditi tim|website=scsport.ba|date=11 August 2023|access-date=12 August 2023|language=bs}}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart===
In July 2024, Demirović moved to [[VfB Stuttgart]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/917796/transfer-karijere-za-zmaja-ermedin-demirovic-je-novi-igrac-stuttgarta|title=Transfer karijere za Zmaja: Ermedin Demirović je novi igrač Stuttgarta|website=avaz.ba|date=16 July 2024|access-date=18 July 2024|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted officially for the side in the [[2024 DFL-Supercup|DFL-Supercup]] fixture against [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] on 17 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/stuttgart-ispustio-trofej-dvije-stative-igrac-vise-i-poraz-od-leverkusena/480276|title=Stuttgart ispustio trofej: Dvije stative, igrač više i poraz na penale od Leverkusena|website=sportsport.ba|date=17 August 2024|access-date=18 August 2024|language=bs}}</ref> A week later, he made his league debut against SC Freiburg and managed to score a goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/demirovic-i-stuttgart-sjajno-poceli-pa-dozivjeli-tezak-poraz-gigovic-bez-minuta-u-porazu-kiela-video|title=Demirović i Stuttgart sjajno počeli pa doživjeli težak poraz, Gigović bez minuta u porazu Kiela|website=n1info.ba|date=24 August 2024|access-date=27 August 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

He debuted in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League#League phase|UEFA Champions League]] away at [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] on 17 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/bayern-postigao-devet-golova-dinamu-demirovic-debitovao-u-madridu-preokret-liverpoola/198020|title=Bayern postigao devet golova Dinamu, Demirović debitovao u Madridu, preokret Liverpoola|website=faktor.ba|date=17 September 2024|access-date=18 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref> Two months later, he scored his first goal in the competition against [[Red Star Belgrade]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/448225-liga-sampiona-zvezda-razbila-stuttgart-pogadjali-krunic-i-demirovic|title=Liga Šampiona: Zvezda razbila Stuttgart, pogađali Krunić i Demirović|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=27 November 2024|access-date=27 November 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

Demirović scored his first career [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] in a victory over [[VfL Bochum]] on 5 April 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/fantasticni-demirovic-postigao-prvi-hat-trick-u-karijeri-i-odveo-stuttgart-do-pobjede/250405064|title=Fantastični Demirović postigao prvi hat-trick u karijeri i odveo Stuttgart do pobjede|website=klix.ba|date=5 April 2025|access-date=6 April 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

He won his first trophy with the club on 24 May, by beating [[Arminia Bielefeld]] in the [[2024–25 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] final.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://raport.ba/ermedin-demirovic-osvojio-prvi-trofej-u-karijeri|title=Ermedin Demirović osvojio prvi trofej u karijeri|website=raport.ba|date=24 May 2025|access-date=27 May 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Demirović represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at all youth levels.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/264434-ermedin-demirovic-vjerujem-da-cu-pokazati-da-nisam-slucajno-ovdje|title=Ermedin Demirović: Vjerujem da ću pokazati da nisam slučajno ovdje|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=15 November 2018|access-date=18 November 2018|language=bs}}</ref>

In November 2018, he received his first senior call up, for a [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League B#Group 3|2018–19 UEFA Nations League B]] game against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] and a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] match against [[Spain national football team|Spain]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/prosinecki-objavio-spisak-na-austriju-i-spaniju-bez-kolasinca-i-todorovica/7882|title=Prosinečki objavio spisak: Na Austriju i Španiju bez Kolašinca i Todorovića|website=faktor.ba|date=2 November 2018|access-date=3 November 2018|language=bs}}</ref> but had to wait until 24 March 2021 to make his debut in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group D|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[Finland national football team|Finland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/remi-na-startu-kvalifikacija-zmajevi-poveli-pa-spasavali-bod-u-helsinkiju|title=Remi na startu kvalifikacija: Zmajevi poveli, pa spašavali bod u Helsinkiju|website=scsport.ba|date=24 March 2021|access-date=27 March 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

On 23 September 2022, in a [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B#Group 3|2022–23 UEFA Nations League B]] tie against [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]], he scored his first senior international goal, which secured the victory for his team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/774419/izboren-je-baraz-za-evropsko-prvenstvo-velika-pobjeda-zmajeva-demirovic-heroj|title=Izboren je baraž za Evropsko prvenstvo: Velika pobjeda Zmajeva, Demirović heroj|website=avaz.ba|date=23 September 2022|access-date=24 September 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Demirović was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Demirović's parents, Nihad and Fatima, are originally from [[Sanski Most]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=U Srbiji reagovali na izjavu Demirovića: "Srpski zet, oženit će Srpkinju" |url=https://raport.ba/u-srbiji-reagovali-na-izjavu-demirovica-srpski-zet-ozenit-ce-srpkinju |access-date=2026-06-06 |website=Raport.ba |language=bs-BA}}</ref> He has a younger brother, Semir. He married his long-time girlfriend Sandra in September 2024. Together they have a daughter named Leana, born in 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/ermedin-demirovic-i-njegova-supruga-sandra-postali-roditelji-djevojcice-leane/250128229|title=Ermedin Demirović i njegova supruga Sandra postali roditelji djevojčice Leane|website=klix.ba|date=28 January 2025|access-date=30 January 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

He is a practising [[Islam|Muslim]]; together with international teammates [[Amar Dedić]], [[Tarik Muharemović]] and [[Dženis Burnić]] he visited a [[mosque]] in [[Sarajevo]] during the national team's concentration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/zmajevi-snimljeni-na-dzumi-dedic-demirovic-muharemovic-i-burnic-bili-u-dzamiji-u-sarajevu/639157|title=Zmajevi snimljeni na džumi: Dedić, Demirović, Muharemović i Burnić bili u džamiji u Sarajevu|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=29 May 2026|access-date=1 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

